journey-map Stealing a Royal Navy Frigate

persona Blackbeard | color: red
  Edward Teach, the most feared pirate in the Caribbean
  Crew of 300 across four vessels, seeking a proper warship

tag Method m
  Cunning(purple)
  Force(red)
  Diplomacy(green)
  Gold(yellow)

[Intelligence]
  Hear tavern rumors of a frigate | 2, m: Cunning
    thought: Every drunk sailor exaggerates — need to verify
    description: A merchant captain mentions HMS Fortune docked for repairs
  Bribe the harbormaster | 1 Nervous, m: Gold
    pain: Harbormaster demands triple the usual rate
    pain: He has been known to double-cross pirates before
    thought: Can we really trust this man with our lives?
  Send a spy disguised as a carpenter | 4 Hopeful, m: Cunning
    description: Israel Hands poses as a shipwright seeking dock work
    opportunity: Our spy could sabotage the ship's defenses from inside
  Map the harbor defenses | 3, m: Cunning
    pain: Two guard boats patrol the entrance after midnight
    thought: The channel is narrow — one wrong move alerts the fort

[Preparation]
  Forge Royal Navy transfer orders | 2 Anxious, m: Cunning
    pain: The Navy seal is nearly impossible to replicate
    thought: If this forgery fails, we hang
    opportunity: A corrupt clerk in Kingston could provide genuine blanks
  Recruit deserters from the garrison | 3, m: Diplomacy
    description: Three marines agree to leave the gate unlocked for a share
    thought: Deserters are useful but never fully trustworthy
  Stockpile weapons in fishing boats | 4, m: Force
    description: Cutlasses and pistols hidden beneath nets and catch
    opportunity: Pre-position boats on both sides of the harbor
  Bribe the night watch with rum | 3, m: Gold
    pain: One guard refuses the bribe and must be dealt with
    thought: Violence draws attention — keep this quiet

[The Heist]
  Create a diversion at the fort | 4 Excited, m: Force
    description: A fire ship drifts into the harbor mouth at 2 AM
    thought: Beautiful chaos — every eye turns to the flames
  Storm the gangway | 2 Terrified, m: Force
    pain: The duty officer sounds an alarm before being subdued
    pain: Two crew members wounded in the initial rush
    thought: No turning back now
  Overwhelm the skeleton crew | 3, m: Force
    description: Forty pirates against eight sleepy sailors — over in minutes
    opportunity: Offer surviving sailors a choice — join or swim
  Cut the anchor cables | 5 Triumphant, m: Force
    thought: The tide is with us — she slips free like a dream
    description: HMS Fortune glides silently past the burning fire ship

[Refit and Rebirth]
  Rename her Queen Anne's Revenge | 5 Proud, m: Diplomacy
    thought: A name to make the Royal Navy tremble
    description: The crew cheers as the new flag rises at dawn
  Mount forty additional cannons | 4, m: Gold
    pain: Quality cannons cost a fortune in the black market
    opportunity: Strip guns from our older captured vessels
  Paint the hull pitch black | 4, m: Force
    description: A black ship emerging from fog is worth a hundred cannons
    thought: Fear is our greatest weapon
  Press-gang skilled sailors | 2 Reluctant, m: Diplomacy
    pain: Forced recruits are resentful and may mutiny
    thought: We need navigators and gunners — volunteers are too few
    opportunity: Offer generous articles — better terms than the Navy pays
  First raid under the new flag | 5 Elated, m: Force
    description: Three merchant ships surrender without a shot fired
    thought: The legend of Blackbeard is born
